cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper proposes an improved cryptographic framework for small aerial drones. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the need to ensure the cyber security of networked aerial drone systems. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper discusses the deployment of cryptographic services in networked drone systems. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper proposes an optimized public key infrastructure (PKI) based framework for small aerial drones. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed framework on an actual small aerial drone.
